THE GAME
--------

  'Xtrings' is a Workbench game where 64 coloured shapes of
different types are all placed, in a 'clothesline' fashion, on a
grid of horizontal and vertical 'strings'. The idea is to move
shapes, by clicking on the board's edges 'loopy thingies', so
shapes make diagonal alignements of at least 4 shapes of the same
type. As 4 or more shapes of the same type are aligned, they are
then removed from the board.

  A feature of the game is that you get points according to the
number of same type shapes that are removed simultaneously...
whether or not they are in the same alignment. So try to remove
as many shapes of the same type as possible. But! Do not leave
between 1 to 3 shapes of any type on the board, as that would
immediately end the game...

  As shapes are removed from the game board, they are not
replaced. When the board is empty, the game displays a new
board with more (up to 8) types of shapes.

  Have fun!

